subclause.text:
provides an adult with an opportunity to
				acquire the general skills, knowledge, and work habits necessary to obtain
				employment;

in which adults perform work for the
				direct benefit of the community under the auspices of public or nonprofit
				organizations;

clause.text:
be
				subject to mandatory participation in work activities specified in paragraph
				(4), except those with 1 or more dependent children under 1 year of age;

1
				adult family member per household who is needed in the home to care for a
				disabled family member;

subclause.text:
baseline
				information relevant to the stated goals and desired outcomes of the pilot
				project;

the impact of the
				interventions on appropriate employment, income, and public benefit receipt
				outcomes among households participating in the pilot project;

equivalent
				information about similar or identical measures among control or comparison
				groups;
